            <fr:addr>forest://erct/erct-0017</fr:addr>
            <fr:route>https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-0017.xml</fr:route>
            <fr:title text="the intrinsic left cleaving of a family of path objects">the intrinsic <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-0031.xml" title="left cleaving of a family of path objects" addr="forest://erct/erct-0031" type="local">left cleaving</fr:link> of a family of <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-0010.xml" title="path object" addr="forest://erct/erct-0010" type="local">path objects</fr:link></fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Example</fr:taxon>
            <fr:meta name="source">
  
  
  <fr:link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-0017.agda" type="external">erct-0017.agda</fr:link>
</fr:meta>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <html:p>Given a type <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex> and a family of <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-0010.xml" title="path object" addr="forest://erct/erct-0010" type="local">path objects</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {B}\colon  A\to  \mathsf {PathObj}]]></fr:tex>, we can always define a <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-0031.xml" title="left cleaving of a family of path objects" addr="forest://erct/erct-0031" type="local">left cleaving</fr:link> of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {B}]]></fr:tex> over the <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-0013.xml" title="the intrinsic path object on a type" addr="forest://erct/erct-0013" type="local">intrinsic path object</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathord {\vartriangle }A]]></fr:tex>. The left cleaving is obtained directly from the transport operation of the identification type.</html:p>
          </fr:mainmatter>
